dismissalText.commentary: Robin Uthappa c Leverock b Jones 3 (4b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: OMG! what a catch by Dwayne Leverock! And what wild celebrations! Let no body say anymore that a fat man can't jump!  Uthappa has a nervous poke, away from the body, at  a length-delivery outside off stump. It flew to the right of  Leverock who hurled himself - hard to visualise, I am not lying but that's what happened- to his right and plucked it single-handed. And the celebrations followed. He ran off to nowhere in particular, changed directions and again went on a jig. The players mobbed him, few other went down in  heap in midwicket in celebration. All over each other. Bermuda are overjoyed. The bowler is the bottom of that heap and hold on .. he is crying. Tears of joy! Meanwhile Leverock is busy giving flying kisses to the crowd! What a start!

commentPostTextItems.html: This is the largest margin of victory, in terms of runs, in the history of one-day internationals. They win by 257 runs. India went into this game, needing to win and win it big. And they have done it. Now all attention will be on Bangladesh v Sri Lanka game. If Bangladesh win, then the race would come down between India and Sri Lanka. If Sri Lanka win against Bangladesh, the net run rate comes into play.  So get out your calculators and get ready to do some maths.

This is Sriram Veera, your commentator of the day, signing off. Please do switch to the West Indies v Zimbabwe game. West Indies require another 71 runs with 6 wickets and 15.4 overs remaining. Brian Lara is in the crease.

dismissalComment.html: OMG! what a catch by Dwayne Leverock! And what wild celebrations! Let no body say anymore that a fat man can't jump!  Uthappa has a nervous poke, away from the body, at  a length-delivery outside off stump. It flew to the right of  Leverock who hurled himself - hard to visualise, I am not lying but that's what happened- to his right and plucked it single-handed. And the celebrations followed. He ran off to nowhere in particular, changed directions and again went on a jig. The players mobbed him, few other went down in  heap in midwicket in celebration. All over each other. milestones.description: David Hemp and Leverock's 44-run partnership is BMUDA's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 27 between Kevin Hurdle and Ryan Steede
Leverock has become the top wicket-taker for BMUDA in ODIs with 21 wickets, going past Mukuddem's 20
Leverock has conceded the most runs in an innings (96) in ODIs for BMUDA, going past Ryan Steede's record of 68
India's 258-run win against Bermuda is the largest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 200-run win against Bangladesh
